SIMPLE: impatience
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impatience
<hw>Im*pa"tience</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>impacience</ets>, F. <ets>impatience</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>impatientia</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality of being impatient; lack
of endurance of pain, suffering, opposition, or delay; eagerness for
change, or for something expected; restlessness; chafing of spirit;
fretfulness; passion; <as>as, the <ex>impatience</ex> of a child or an
invalid</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I then, . . . ⟦br⟧
Out of my grief and my <qex>impatience</qex>,⟦br⟧
Answered neglectingly.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With huge <qex>impatience</qex> he inly swelt⟦br⟧
More for great sorrow that he could not pass,⟦br⟧
Than for the burning torment which he felt.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 734 --></p>

<p><ent>Impatiency</ent>⟦br⟧
